%N A193716 Decimal expansion of Pi^3*log(2)/24 - 3*Pi*zeta(3)/16.
%C A193716 The absolute value of Integral_{x=0..Pi/2} x^2*log(sin(x)) dx or (d^2/da^2 (Integral_{x=0..Pi/2} cos(ax)*log(sin(x)) dx)) at a=0. The absolute value of (Sum_{n>=1} (lim_{ a -> 0} (d^2/da^2 (sin((a+2n)*Pi/2)/n/(a+2n)))))-(Pi/2)^3*log(2)/3. - _Seiichi Kirikami_ and _Peter J. C. Moses_
%D A193716 I. S. Gradshteyn and I. M. Ryzhik, Table of Integrals, series and Products, 1.441.2, 4th edition, log(sin(x))=-(sum {1..infinity} cos(2nx)/n)-log(2).
%H A193716 Richard E. Crandall and Joe P. Buhler,, <a href="https://projecteuclid.org/euclid.em/1048515810">On the evaluation of Euler sums</a>, Exper. Math. 3 (4) (1994) 275 (discuss Integral_{x=0..1} x^n*cot(x) dx which is obtained by partial integration).
%H A193716 Shin-ya Koyama and Nobushige Kurokawa, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1090/S0002-9939-04-07863-3">Euler’s integrals and multiple sine functions</a>, Proc. Amer. Math. Soc. 133(2005), 1257-1265.
%F A193716 Equals A091925*A002162/24-3*A000796*A002117/16.
%F A193716 Equals (1/3) * Integral_{x=0..1} arcsin(x)^3/x dx = (1/3) * Integral_{x=0..Pi/2} x^3/tan(x) dx. - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 24 2026
